<TITLE> Govt to make land transfer easy: minister </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Sherpur, Feb 6 (bdnews24.com)  The government will take measures to help people easily transfer land ownership, the land minister said Friday. Field-level officials have been directed to make sure people don't have to pay bribe, Rezaul Karim Hira told reporters after a prize-giving ceremony at two educational institutions in Nokla Upazila in Sherpur district. The minister said the traditional systems for land survey and management will be replaced by modern and scientific systems. To that end, he said, digital land survey has already started at five mouzas of Savar Upazila. He said the government land distribution activities among the landless people will be strengthened in phases. bdne
